         <div class="spacer-large"></div>
        <div class="blog-content  message-body">
		    <p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"3... 2... connection restored." Scrap said over the phone as he jacked the PIX firewall back onto the Internet.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"Hold on to your ponies!" I exclaimed as I right-clicked on the suspect E-mail and selected "scan attachment".</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">Within seconds event viewer was showing a service failure by the anti-virus scanning service and a quick restart.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"Scrap - confirmed. The anti-virus service just reloaded itself after the scan. You should see a..." I said but was cut off by Scrap.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"BAM! There it went. Just saw that ping post go sailing by. Here comes the reply. Traffic levels are increasing. It's the same as before. I think we can safely say that we isolated the issue." Scrap announced on the phone.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"Pull the plug. Strategy meeting in the IT conference room in five minutes. Let's round everyone up." I barked as I disconnected the call and looked around for my notebook. Things were about to get even more interesting.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">Cedric and I wandered down to the conference room and met Scrap, Cookie and Kip. I pulled out a chair from the end of the conference room table and jumped right in.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"We are at the moment of decision, folks. We have established what is causing the network outages and we're nearly complete in our assessment of how much damage has been done to the machines on both this network and your neighbors' networks. Obviously these companies can't stay removed from the internet forever. We need to.. well, you need to make a decision on how you want this situation dealt with." I said.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">Kip maintained eye contact with me and nodded in understanding.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"Scrap and I are going to suggest two approaches to your situation. One is cheap and quick, the other is expensive and will take a good deal of time. Here are your options. Scrap, please do the honors."</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">Scrap shifted his weight in his chair and cleared his throat. "The first option is to have us take a tactical approach to the problem. We're going to need to fix the issue on the mail servers and then clean them of any malware or cruft. If we determine that they are not salvageable, then we'll need to reload and rebuild them. At that point we'll need to take a similar approach to all the workstations. Only after a thorough review and certification process should any machine go live on your network."</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">I scanned the room and noted that everyone was aware of that requirement.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"The second option is that we treat this like a crime scene. The network would stay locked down and forensic copies of all affected machines will be made. Research would be done to determine if this was an isolated case of an errant bogon E-mail, or if this was a targeted attack. During our research we would work with your staff to implement the salvage operations in the previous option after we have determined that no additional evidence can be gathered at the scene." Scrap concluded.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">Kip's left leg was bouncing up and down and he was pinching his lips with his right forefinger and thumb. After a few seconds of contemplation he sat straight up in his chair and looked directly at me.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Verdana; font-size: 16px;">"Option two. I need to know!"</span></p>

		    <div class="clear"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="spacer"></div>
